  <section>
    <h2>Drawer Variants</h2>
    <p>Use <code>data-position</code> to turn any dialog into a slide-in drawer panel. No additional JavaScript required &mdash; drawers inherit all dialog features: Invokers API, ESC to close, focus trapping, backdrop.</p>

    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/dialog-drawers.html" url="dialog-drawers.html" title="Drawer variants" shadow></browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Drawer markup">{{ drawerCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Position</th>
          <th>Use Case</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-position="end"</code></td>
          <td>Right (in LTR)</td>
          <td>Navigation, settings panels</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-position="start"</code></td>
          <td>Left (in LTR)</td>
          <td>Sidebar, filters</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-position="bottom"</code></td>
          <td>Bottom</td>
          <td>Mobile action sheets, share menus</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-position="top"</code></td>
          <td>Top</td>
          <td>Banners, announcements</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p>Slide animations respect <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code>, falling back to a simple fade.</p>
  </section>

